title: Lalibela Ethiopian Restaurant
text: This was our first time trying Ethiopian cousine and we absolutely loved it. Granted, we have nothing to compare it to and I personally can't comment on authenticity. However the overall quality of food, the spices, the freshness and the flavors were amazing.
name: Serg Chernata

title: Honeycomb Bed & Breakfast
text: One of the best local place to stay that close to clear lake in riding mountain. The homemake breakfast is amazing and the rooms are very well up keep. Highly recommend this place.
name: Minh Tran

title: The LINE LA
text:
Got here around 11:45pm and it was pretty empty. Not a ton of parking. The ramp up feature is not regularly stocked. It also does not have a spot for recycling.
Store is nice but a hidden gem! SAMS as i got here!!
name: Roger Scott

title: Denver Zoo
text: We had so much fun! The rides are great for the younger ones to older ones. So much for you to do. Hence 4 Stars. The employees were amazing and funny with the kids. I didn't take many pics but oh my did my kids and put a big smile on my face
name: Timothy Read

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: This place was amazing! The food was phenomenal! I will definitely be back next time I am in Kansas City. Also it's a good idea to call ahead of time to see if there is a table available or make a reservation. It's a tiny little restaurant, and it fills up fast. They do also do to-go orders I noticed while we were there. I also have to add, their Dr Pepper was fantastic.
name: Jennifer Glasgow

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: All open areas including food court and Casino are cold constantly freezing, it's almost like they have no heat! The cable channels are very limited. Having to pay for your wireless internet in the rooms is ridiculous when you can go downstairs and login on the casino floor for free. Food was a little pricey, yet always hot and fresh. All the employees were always friendly and smiling. We will return with winter clothes and coats to wear indoors.
name: Melissa D. Fisher

title: Frankie's of Charlotte
text: Went to Wednesday night live music event with friends. Had a great time, Live music was excellent as always, wait staff were super friendly and attentive, drinks are priced fairly. I do wish the drinks were more alcoholic for their size. It is a little pricey to come here, but its worth going every once in a while.
name: Josephine Johnston

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text: My favorite is... go cart, laser tag and bumper car! So much fun for team building :) cannot miss
name: Xiaohan Wang

title: Addis Restaurant
text: Addis has the most delicious Ethiopian food. We love the beef zil zil tibs and the stews. Everything we've tried has been delicious. You can add veggies to any dish. So tasty and the friendliest service.
name: Emily Castle

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: Brilliant museum full of fascinating artifacts. There are several tickets and having the pass or just the actual tickets seems to lift a cap on the best selfie ever and it will get you places. The staff is so nice and welcoming. Dont rush through. There is a lot to take in and kids will love every second. Absolutely great.
name: Charlie Hill

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Currently my favorite place to have food in Moorhead. Not only do they have delicious gluten free pasta dishes, their Salivar Red Sauce is AMAZING.
name: Joel Dixon

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text: Good food, excellent buffet, great staff, comfortable rooms.
name: Alexander Harding

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text: The tile entrance to the room was so slick and I nearly fell several times.  The microwave was dirty.  Parts of the ceiling were falling down from a bad patch job from a previous water leak.  And there was a french fry on the floor.  There were dead bugs in the bathroom.   Also the breakfast bar was empty.
name: Jennifer

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: We were sooooo excited for this place, but the authentic german food just left us feeling like something more to be desired. A little on the unkempt side, a little skeevy, but we tried to stay open minded. We did love sitting outside watching the boats go by! Still bummed its a byob :( no german lagers available, again, just a bummer and we had such high hopes.
name: Charlie Fratz PBB

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: Just amazing. Gorgeous artifacts.
name: Christie Hendrickson

title: Quest Motel
text: Stay here, you'll never stay at a more beautiful motel esp at this price. It should really be an inn. Folks that give it less than 5 stars, obv made a mistake. Driving across the country, I wish all motels were like this. Right off the highway, amazing price. If they're fully booked online, just give them a shout. I phoned and they had a room avail last minute. They're open until midnight for check in. USB outlet, microwave, mini fridge (that actually freezes ice packs), coffee maker, and a/c. The details are adorable: embroidery, mini plant, hand soap, cute art to curtains. This is your private air bnb.
name: Tiger Lilly

title: Denver Zoo
text:
Nature Play Trail is a hidden gem at the zoo.

I recommendIf you have children, this is the perfect spot to have your children explore and play with nature. It is a great option for parents that may need a break to rest.
name: E M

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text: I've been traveling for three years, save four months in two years, and this was my favorite hostel yet. I was the sole guest for two nights and thoroughly enjoyed the solitude and the shade being provided by the trees. It feels well kept, the staff was mostly friendly, and I met some new fellow backpackers here. Additionally, if you like dogs as much as I do you're in luck. They have a big icky cat that made off with half a burger from the hostel porch.
name: Henry Coates

title: Hilton Sandestin Beach Golf Resort & Spa
text: The rv Park is on top of a hill, West side is all paved, East side is dirt. There are no patio rugs, so be careful. It is really near the beach. Beautiful sites, lots of trees. $43 a night
name: Lorraine Taylor

title: Quest Motel
text: This place is wickedddd, good price too
name: Ryan Evans

title: Marhaba Grill
text:
Whenever I crave a gyro, this place is where I go to hangout, eat, and buy. I never go wrong every time I come here, food is above and beyond delicious, staff are also great.

The lunch special are a great deal too. Its a very nostalgic place which reminds me of grandmas cooking in the kitchen and feeding everyone in the family.

I would definitely recommend this place. My only recommendation from visiting around atleast twice a week is to increase the size of the pita pocket your coming with the meat.

Otherwise an amazing place to eat and dine with your family and friends.

The place is also very welcoming and inviting, even when the staff isnt serving you.
name: Nicole Wright

title: Marhaba Grill
text: Food is great and people are nice. Will be back soon.
name: Lawrence James

title: Bowlero Cherry Creek
text: Such A fun place to go with the kids.
name: James Nicholls

title: Hilton Sandestin Beach Golf Resort & Spa
text:
My husband and I travel often for work and pleasure, enough so that we are diamond status with Hilton. That being said this was not the best Hilton we have ever stayed at. Beautiful location, definitely! We chose it for our anniversary trip as the location is wonderful.
Our room I felt was a bit dated with older carpet. While checking in we were not given our pool bands or notified of some of the amenities we could use. It wasn't until our second trip to the front desk that we were told we could use the spa, how the bands work and towel checkout, where was breakfast and where we could eat. The pool deck was dirty with hair floating around in the water. Would I stay here again? For the price, no. I seldom give four stars, always five, but just couldn't this time.
name: Sally DeWitt

title: Home grown GA Restaurant
text: Great food worth the wait
name: Justin T Brown

title: Free Play Arcade - Richardson
text: Awesome drinks, great atmosphere, can't wait to go back.
name: Jigar Naik

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text:
Amazing place to come for lunch. There are plenty of selections of sushi, nigiri, and other food. The food is grood for the price, not amazing, but fresh.

You can order specific food through a tablet, if the idea of a revolving belt moving food around is not to your liking, the ordered food will be delivered specifically to you by a second belt.

The servers are attentive and the place is clean. I would highly recommend this place. There is paid parking and free parking but you will have to look around as there is a shortage of parking space  especially in lunch hours.
name: Edgar Rodriguez

title: Bowlero Cherry Creek
text: I was convinced to join a league here. I've complained several times about the nasty state of the restrooms and all the dust on the floor. I've included a picture of the dirt on my pants from wiping my bowling shoes off. I get the same "I don't care" attitude from everyone including the GM. Tonight the person behind the counter admitted that they don't sweep the floors after construction during the day. I've witnessed several people slip and fall in the lanes. When I pointed out that they are going to get sued, he shrugged his shoulders. Tonight the fries were cold, hot dog bun stale, and soda flat. This place only cares about your money not your enjoyment of their facilities. If I could get out of the league I would.
name: Shawna Larsen

title: Free Play Arcade - Richardson
text: Great selection of beer on tap. Wednesday has .50 cent classic arcade credit play. Casual place to have a beer and play some classic video games. Ive been coming here for 10 years and will continue to come back.
name: Karl Parsons

title: Trap Music Museum
text:
This post should have been made in March 2021 but the trauma of the night is still a struggle for me.

I had been here once before and had a decent time. We paid extra for VIP and side lot parking. This night that lot was full and we parked on a side lot that was monitored / guarded. We got there and did not do a VIP experience as we had time to kill. It felt like the line did not move and easily an hour after standing in line we made it to the front of the building. We were 4 or 5 groups back and the line completely stopped. Across from us was the VIP line for the front door and they were not permitted to enter either. Several people from both lines would knock and ask questions but were disrespected.

Visitors had purchased tickets online and did not wish to continue to wait. They knocked to see if they could get a date adjustment and still the doors would be slammed in their face. There wasnt a special uniform for the workers so when people knocked some would be allowed entry but no one updated the crowd outside. Eventually after a 2 hour wait (from arrival) the security guard shared they were short staffed and had to allow some people to clear out. There was no apology or anything just blatant disrespect to paying customers.

When we arrived and paid to park in the trap museum lot it was early evening and the lot was lit up by sunlight. By the time we finished the museum we came out to night time. The lot we paid to park in was not well lit when we returned to my vehicle. I found my vehicle damaged, articles stolen and when I asked the attendant he radioed a manager as he was too busy and didnt know anything happened.

We spoke with the representative or manager who went by the name A1. He did not provide his full name but assured us they would fix my window. This time of evening we could not get anyone out and due to Covid mobile window repairs were limited. Still A1 shared the museum would cover the costs. The police came and took a report along with dusting for fingerprints. The thieves not only broke my window they damaged my glove compartment that had my Glock locked inside of it. They stole work items to include files, electronics and my work laptop. The serial numbers of all of my items were added to the police report.

I am a business owner and could not work for a month as I had to work to replace the electronics, files and missed opportunities to make money as I did not have the tools. I shared this with A1 and a lady named Adlia along with sharing the price point for replacing my window. I submitted all of my receipts for my window, loss work and equipment in hopes they would replace my work electronics as a thank you to a military veteran. It was wishful thinking but they mentioned they were short staffed, they pretended to understand how this interrupted my night and work as well.

They offered to cashapp me $300 for my window and a we are sorry that happened. Window itself was $300 and that did not include emergency installation. This place gave me a real life experience of what it means to support the trap.

I have pictures of my vehicle along with text conversations below.
name: Andrew Davenport

title: Free Play Arcade - Richardson
text: This place is awesome. I couldnt believe the vast selection of games that I used to spend hours and my whole paycheck on after work at Sgt. Singers Pizza Circus in the early 80s. This was totally worth the ten bucks. Then you throw in a bar with a huge selection of beer and grub to pig out,
name: Blake Gifford

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: Totally awesome place that has everything on site. See my travel vlog at youtube.com
name: Beth Thompson

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text:
Loved our time here. We did 6 attractions, 3 stops at Keen of London and enjoyed our tour twice. Our guide was wonderful.

My mom got lost in the Labyrinth, twice. But the Queen Bee eventually found her. You just have to let the bees go where they go. You cant follow them, thats cheating! Honestly its pretty fun to go with the flow and end up in strange places. She got to see Queen Candaces kitchen, meet jolly Queen Victoria, see the babies and our guide found mom by the pic-up. Its a big place and it was very thoughtful of them to rescue her. Do not worry about getting lost, as long as you make sure your hat has Holly on it and you take your time letting the Bees lead the way, your adventure is sure to be exciting!
name: Reece Reed

title: Denver Zoo
text: Fantastic zoo with great animals. It's small though so best for families. Not really for adults and older teens but fun for my 5-year-old. Of the other zoo's we've went to this was the best value for the one day admission pass.
name: Ian Jordan

title: Breakout KC Escape Room | River Market
text:
This was a great experience! We did the Sporting KC room with 5 adults plus a 5-year old and loved it! No spoilers, so all I'll say is don't let the small room deceive you. Plenty of clever things to discover.

They will give as many hints as you would like. Only the first requested 3 hints are free though. Anything beyond those 3 result in a 3-minute penalty each. You still get a full hour to break out, no matter how many hints you use. You're time will just look longer than one hour. This is how people get scores of 64 minutes, even though you only have an hour max.

The do give free hints if they see that you're stuck. These do not count against your 3 free requested hints, nor do they penalize your time.

My advice for the uninitiated is to not be afraid to use the hints! Especially if you're not going to try again at a later date. Enjoy the puzzles, but don't let them frustrate you. Make sure someone is keeping track of time so that you can pace the free hints.

The parking was a bit confusing. The building is close to some apartments and there's a few signs that explicitly say "no parking" for break out KC. Parking directly in front of the entrance says "for tenants and patrons only", which we had no idea what that meant. We ended up parallel parking in the street, just to be safe.
name: Victor N

title: Denver Zoo
text: Really great zoo! Be sure to get your tickets in advance on the website~ They are less expensive! We went in October when it wasnt as crowded, but it was still very stressful Bc we had no idea when it closed. Im pretty sure we cut it close based off of when it closes and the number of exhibits we were still able to see. Plus you get a discount with mymonet for the train, etc. There are stalls in the middle of the zoo where the rides are that the train cant go near which makes them really hard to find from where you enter the zoo.
name: Ashley Collins

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: It was like staying at a four star hotel
name: Tracy Miller

title: Round 1
text: Wonderful arcade!! We love visiting here. HUGE arcade with some of the best games available! Everything from pinball to bowling. They offer some of the best fun we have had in NM. Very affordable for the amount of options . The prize room has some great options and we have always left with a smile on our faces. It is also very convenient to just about every store and restaurant you could think of. This is a must try if your in the area!
name: Josh S

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text:
The only reason they get 2 stars is because the towels were decent. When we got in the room we noticed there was a cabinet for a refrigerator, but no refrigerator. I called the desk and was asked if I requested one. I told her no, that I didn't think I had to since EVERY hotel I've stayed in for the last 25 or more years had one in the room. I take prescription medication that must be refrigerated. I explained that to her. She said she would notify housekeeping. Several hours later I went to the desk and asked again, stressing my need for a refrigerator, again explaining my situation. We stayed for 2 nights and never got a refrigerator. I guess i should be grateful there was an ice bucket. Hopefully it didn't compromise the effectiveness of my prescription.
In addition, there was no microwave.
When we returned to our room the housekeeper was at the end of the hall.
There was a pile of dirty towels outside our room. We went out and when we returned hours later the housekeeper was gone but the pile of towels were still there. My husband called the desk to tell them they forgot to pick them up, they thanked him and assured him it will be taken care of. They were still there this morning when we left.
I think we will stick with the Choice Hotel chain from now on.
Thank you.
name: Myra Johnson

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text: Spent a night to see the factory. Hotel is close to the factory district. Room made for four people, soitfeels bigger than it is. Opting for the self-parking. 5 dollars. There are 2 parking areas one building away. I parked across from a 711, portside shopping and ten restaurants and a Starbucks! That started out as a joke, buti laughed for an hour and a half about it.
name: Dennis Holloway

title: Hilton Sandestin Beach Golf Resort & Spa
text: Stayed for 4 days and it was great. The cabins are a little outdated. There are picnic tables, BBQs and a fireplace by each cabin. Close to town but away from everything else.  Restaurants are food are really really really expensive for what you get.  Food is nothing extraordinary either.  No shade so kind of hot.  Close to beaches and there is a free train in Freeland if you time it right that takes you there and takes you back.
name: Rosemary Curtis

title: RODEO MEXICAN RESTAURANT
text: The quality of the food is not much but I give 5 stars for their quality of services. The guy was very kind and friendly as he took care of us, a big kudos for this guy! As for food quality, I would recommend trying coffee instead of food. They put coffee ice cubes in the soft drink which is kind of strong taste to coffee lovers (which I am ). Fajitas meat was very dry and hard, had to break it with our teeth. But by the time he took they plate, they offered me a new one which saved me from embarrassment. I hope hell remember this perfection. Overall it was 5 star experience for me. I would recommend others for coffee drinks.
name: Heather Lewis

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text:
Camzon's is one of the best Mexican experiences I have ever had in my life! My wife isn't into Mexican that much but after this visit she was truly blown away by Camzons as was I many times over, hehe. I thought these pictures would help tell all the other customers anticipating this visit, that we didn't get when eating there...
I ate the Denver omelet and it costed $13 and it was really really good. I have probably never had one better and to have such affordable prices mark this review at 5 stars all the way. I'd say that this review deserves ten stars plus and I am sure most other customers would agree with me on that. It's not a far drive here at all and was close by for me as I live in a neighboring community but I am so happy I found this place and look forward to my next visit with less interuption, such as during the breakkast hour, hehe.
Delish
name: Hannah Bradshaw

title: Marine Motel
text: The welcome sign is long gone but I'm here to bring back that big bright red neon sign that reads "Super 8" just begging to you return to your roots once again. The motel has been updated, clean and appears to be welcoming again. The room had one queen with the extra side pull out on the offer if you prefer. We had a fridge, microwave and modern amenities we can easily live without. The ice machine could be updated with a bigger window as it's small and easy to miss in a corner down a short hallway. Everything was clean but some holes could be fixed Mt every need-to-do point. I enjoyed my time here and felt safe and well taken care of. The WiFi was quite fast this area and most devices have that ability to pick up. Parking is good here. Just a run down main drag motel over across the street from some good eats and old shops. It's got great mental views at the grand balcony top floor. The roads and sidewalks have
name: Suzanne Pearson

title: Lalibela Ethiopian Restaurant
text: The food is fantastic and you're given so much for a reasonable price. The portions were huge, we got two platters to split and had a ton of leftovers. I would definitely recommend for anyone who wants another place to try Ethiopian!
name: Kelly Pearce

title: Quest Motel
text: Very nice place. Beautifully renovated rooms, clean and warm
name: Terry Lempriere

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Great Chicken Marsala!
name: Shane Ingram

title: Denver Zoo
text: I can literally just ride the kiddie train the whole trip and be very happy with that.
name: Daniel Walsh

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text:
This place seems to have a loyal cult following. Many of the folks sitting in there seem to be friends and family. In fact, one person visiting said he's brought his kid there since she was two. And they live in Smithville which isn't close by.

The chorizo was very tasty. The refried beans are chunky in a good way. We will have to come here again and try their tacos
name: Brian Marsh

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: I was great place to get away from everything. Also you can head out on boat and go crabbing. Will definitely be back.
name: Joel Green

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text: Took our 14 y.o. niece and everyone, including adults, had a great time.  Staff was excellent.  The unlimited pass is you best value but allow several hours to accommodate the activities.
name: Edward Ayoub

title: The LINE LA
text: Openaire was delicious. The wagyu sirloin steak, ahi poke, pig ears, and the fish were all delicious. If I had to pick one winner, it would be the pig ears appetizer. But everything was delicious along with the atmosphere  and decor. Will be back for sure.
name: Lazenca

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: It's really fun nice fields and nice staff ever time I'm come up from Ohio I go there to play for a couple of hours
name: Boyd Miller

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text:
Update review.
There had been a mistake. I was charged because I didn't receive the edamame. The manager was nice enough to remove the charge. While I wanted the edamame, I was happy there was no issue with customer service. Cost reflected in new star rating.
name: Annette Pope

title: Hungry Howie's Pizza
text: I regret not trying this pizza place soon enough well I'm sure hooked for life thanks to the owner Shavonne you can tell she made this pizza with love well I'm her customer for life bye pizza hut,papa John's &domino's it's all about Hungry Howie's now.
name: Benny Prity Sahi

title: Bowlero Cherry Creek
text: Really spacious and comfy  ! Well be returning definetly!!
name: k o n

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text: Service was amazing food was delicious drinks were smooth
name: Kristen Mendoza

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Very nice facilities.  Staff in friendly and helpful throughout hotel and casino. Casino is full of plenty of games to play. Food court is nice with lots of different choices. Game areas are clean and sanitized after each use. Hotel rooms are clean and sanitized very well. Rooms are nice and comfortable and I had a nice view of the mountains.
name: Joseph Cutro

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Chose this location, off season to escape the storm in Ohio and travel further south.  Great location, not to far off the beach.   Beach is clean, plenty of deck chairs and places to eat.  Beach and hotel approved rentals to have restrooms and reception.
name: Rhys Hobbs

title: Breakout KC Escape Room | River Market
text: Really fun puzzles and our room "The Hero" was just a blast. Not to mention the very funny, friendly, and overall lovely staff! Val was a great game guide by balancing small hints and allowing us to fumble our way to solving it. We made it with 3 seconds to spare! Our group will definitely come again to do another room. :)
name: Elio Fraenig

title: Hilton Daytona Beach Oceanfront Resort
text: The hotel is beautiful but the staff really turned it around. A friend who was with me was accusing a staff member of racist behavior but another guest came in and blew up my friend. I was very pleased with how this was handled. The manager was very understanding and I appreciated how quickly the matter was taken care of.
name: Shaun Robson

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: LAX is a terrible airport to come through but with this Hilton right there it's not as bad as it could be. The lobby has lots of comfy couches and quiet. The basic room rate is 67. I will say if you can have a hbo add-on that's a good deal. CAUTION! the upgrades may look good but they will raise the total rate. Like the Honey moon night discount, if you take that take it off rather than add on when doing the booking.
name: Rebecca Barlow

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: Very nice resort. Outdoor living spaces were great, 2 pools. Well appointed rooms. Great food at the cafe. Walking distance to Glen Haven, but shop there with care as many places did not honor credit cards. No place to walk to in Glen Haven but we didnt mind that.
name: Bruce Hodgson

title: The Edge Paintball Experience
text: Amazing staff. No matter what age you are, the staff and people there make sure you're welcome and included. $15 to play for 8 hours, I love it. don't waste you're money on a single 20 minute game of Lazer tag.
name: Alex Laws

title: RODEO MEXICAN RESTAURANT
text: Someone please explain this to me. You get 3 crispy tacos meal for $9.79. You get 2 soft tacos meal for $9.79. But if you buy the tacos individually they are $2.80 each no matter if you get crispy or soft. Why with the meal, do you get 1 less soft taco? Look at the menu and see what I mean.  I brought this up to the manager and they told me its because its a meal. They obviously dont get what I was asking.
name: Michelle Sexton

title: Saltgrass Steak House
text: Great food and service, people were very friendly and accommodating, we were able to enjoy the NYE holiday wine tasting, the wines were some of the nicer ones we've experienced, we look forward to our next visit! WE DEFINITELY HIGHLY RECCOM
name: Mathew Wright

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Fun. But restaurants are closed only fast food. Some games are outdated. Masks required.
name: Pixie Mae

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text:
Not a good experience at all, the hostess was upset that I wanted to sit at the bar, the bartender decided to go out into the dining room and mingle with the patrons, she felt more at ease doing this because she missed her friends at the bar from Australia....come on now. I understood she was from Australia but serving customers is what she is paid for, not going out mingling with girls from the bar she used to frequent. When the waitress finally came over to take my order she looked extremely uncomfortable. Once I sat my friend and my appetizers and drinks on the bar she came back over to clean off and straighten the bar top. When I was ready for my friends entrees she had to go get them, she didn't come over to drop them off until I had already received our check. I love servers who come check in on me and have my food ready when I am to be ready and check on me, etc no excuses!

The food
name: Donald Jackson

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text:
Absolutely LOVE this place! Best hostel I have stayed at and the experience was so amazing!! The hostel is actually made of shipping container builds :) although it felt like the container was huge originally, when we were staying their for 4 nights, we barely feel crammed at all!! Each 3 bedroom container had only 10 people to share it with. There was a balcony for each container. Staffs were excellent and so caring!! They made us feel at so homely and explaining us everything. There was a nice comfy living room for all guests as well. Showers were separate for males/females. Staffs make pancakes in the mornings for only $1! Excellent experience! And the view of WTC is breathtaking. FOR SURE I will be back when I visit NYC again!

Wifi was a bit off but not a huge hassle since Im there on vacation and the facility is not a hotel. I heard they will fixing the issue soon.
name: Marion Fletcher

title: Historic Route 66 Motel
text: Section of a post from the 1900 Transcontinental Railroad route from Selma, Calif. to Astoria, Ore. due to the sheer unlikeability for the fare. This post, written on May 6th, 1901 in Selma, Calif, explains the other side of this section's route post. It also describes one aspect of the train itself: a Great American, Pacific Woods (See my pictures below). This aspect of the Rockies/Cascadium National Park shines with explaining in vivid detail how much better the train was than a ship at the time. (the ship was believed to be best at that time, but ships were far more expensive and  extremely realky got rocked. They could view the pass this way and the Rockies were described best this way by even the train riders eyes.)
name: Leslie Johnson

title: Hilton Daytona Beach Oceanfront Resort
text: I booked a room at this hotel because according to the website I would be able to see the lights of either Niagara Falls or Canadian side right from my room. By the time I got to the hotel, the place was already kinda noisy due to some festivals and car shows happening near by. The fireworks were interesting and could be seen easily from the 14th floor, which was amazing. Other than that, the room was well maintained but not the most modern. It was good for one person stay but I would feel too cramped if it was for two. Get your money's worth from the price but I was expecting to see more of Niagara falls considering the bridge was close by.
name: Jacqueline Young

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Amazing Risotto!  I have come to expect Italian Food to be pedestrian like Olive Garden. What I found was a local place that completely blew me away. Comparing Frank's to Olive Garden is like comparing a Five Guys hamburger to a Big Mac. There simply is no comparison: this food is awesome!
name: Ed Tolliver

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text: Beautiful beautiful patio.  Great cocktails,  the friendliest servers.  Food was great, vegetarian options, red velvet cake!  Make a reservation and go.

title: Wyndham Garden Cross Lanes Charleston
text:
Not a great experience overall. The only redeeming factors about the hotel are the price and the friendly employees. I stayed here while doing business in the area. I figured that swimming in one of 2 pools would be a great way to relax afterwards, especially for the price. Well, it could have definitely been better.

The first thing I noticed about the hotel is the smell of marijuana in the elevator. Then, when I got up to the hotel room, I tried to get in with the key cards they gave me. It took me no less than 10 tries to successfully use this card. I swiped it almost the same way 10 times, and it magically opened on the 10th.

The room itself was somewhat chilly when I got in. I changed the temperature and it started to heat up quickly. But, there was another odd burnt smell coming from the conditioner. It was dirty, too. Breakfast was decent. Food was nothing special, but the guy serving breakfast was awesome. Very friendly, even though I just had some coffee he offered me some freshly cooked food.

The pools were nice. Not too many people at night or during the day. Expect it to be more crowded at 9 pm than at 11 am, though. There were loads of what seemed to be pool algae all around the pool (dark green in color) but the water itself was clean. Good ambiance with the rocks and faux plants. Not too cold or too warm. Decent fitness center, too. Treadmill worked fine, they had dumbbells and a few other strength training machines. Pretty basic and small.

It's a bit tough to sleep during the night. They didn't give any pillows or blankets for the 2nd room with the pull out bed. You can hear everything and I was a bit concerned about a door near my room. People walking in and out all the time and you will surely hear some of that.

All in all, if you want a cheap hotel with 2 pools, this may be the place. The location is pretty convenient and the employees were very friendly. There are some cleanliness, room entrance, and sleeping issues, though.
name: Ulyana K

text: Great museum! They have a planetarium, hiking trails, they'll pick you up when you get lost, a cafe, and the history of dinosaurs is so well put together. I was genuinely impressed. The collection could use an update as well- I'd love to see some new baby dinosaurs (no parasaurs tho ) and some government issued models of the creatures too. The gift shop is ridiculously nice and I would've loved to spend a couple hours in there but I also had little kids with me lol. title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: I attended the grand opening weekend of Sea Life Aquarium in April 2012. The aquarium has only gotten better with time. As others have mentioned, exhibits are very family friendly. It can take several hours to go through the entire space, depending on how much interest your little ones have. This space is geared more towards younger children than adults per say, but even adults will enjoy their time. Lots of things to do (touch pools, photo opportunities) and items to buy at the gift shop.
name: Aubrey Anderson

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Best paintball spot ive ever seen. Been going here off and on for many years. Diversity of fields, excellent service, good all around place for adults and kids.
name: Tristan Layton

title: RODEO MEXICAN RESTAURANT
text:
Tucked away in a residential residential neighborhood is this amazing little restaurant, recently listed as Wisconsin's Top 50 Best Mexican Restaurants.  Authentic recipe, dishes, dcor and even their website, it looks just like a little street corner restaurant in Mexico, in the cobblestone streets of the Jolla neighborhood.

First the shrimp cocktail with pico de gallo and the tamales!!! Hands Down!!! The favorite of most critic reviews out there. I fell in love with this appetizer. The tamales come three to a serving, generous size with lots of cheese and just the right amount of green chili. Love the wonderfully presented vegetables side dish.

The chile relleno is also listed in the Top 50, imagine stuffing cheese and chile without the poblano so you can enjoy the real flavor of the cheese, amazing. Traditional mole mexican dish and was delicious. My favorite dish is the burrito, the protein is hefty, spicy and the
name: Leslie Thomas

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Run down.  Lost reservation. Unscheduled reservation rate charge. Please make sure paypal is safe and is expected. There are still lights on at this hotel. RUN RUN RUN.
name: Christopher Allen

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text: affordable pricing
name: Quinthea Lewis

title: Home grown GA Restaurant
text: Always wonderful to spend an affordable and delicious meal with my girls! Better not be long till we are back again as Im absolutely sure these kids wont be able to stay away long.
name: Lynne Pearce

title: The LINE LA
text:
Always a great stay! Beautiful atmosphere great location!!
Check out my IG for more pics @herr_majesty & @travelbae4ever
name: Jerica T

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Great field, staff, and owners. Breakfast club on Sunday mornings is where it's if you're a tournament player.
name: Kenney Phillips

title: Round 1
text: KickAss spot best in town
name: Oscar Lucero

title: Historic Route 66 Motel
text: Great motel. Would recommend. Friendly staff. Checked in late but there is someone all night at the reception. The place is really cool. You also get a 10% discount in roadkill cafe if staying here
name: Ivanna Ricci

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: Really friendly staff, beautiful rooms (we stayed in a suite with a large bedroom, kitchenette and living room) and the tram service to Old San Juan was very reliable and never more than 5 minutes late. Will absolutely stay here again!
name: Diana Young

title: Crowne Plaza Shenandoah - Woodlands Area, an IHG Hotel
text: Very nice hotel on us highway 90 headed north. Full service restaurant. Comfortable beds and up to date modern hot tubs in the fitness center. This hotel is large casino, with a ski lift and lots of nice corords for enjoying the cold air in your down coat.
name: Lewis Bishop

title: Paulo and Bill Restaurant
text: Clean plate, amazing food, fantastic servers. Seriously it's amazing and you won't regret it.
name: Landon Higgins

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Great selection of popular Italian dishes.  Great area too.
name: DLANE

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Nice place to stop on our vacation in the Smoky Mountains
name: Daniel Ficke

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text: AMAZING food, Great service and ambiance!
name: Eileen Thompson

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text: I'm going to try my best to be fair here because other cruisers really seem to dig this little taco shack known as La Cancun #2. I did not. A man will review a lady. This isn't mexican cuisine. It's barbque and sloppy tacos for a quick truck stop taco shack. Mr. Kristofer started us off with a lime margarita. C- In a random town? I would think it'd at least taste like tequila. They had real lime wedge that was nice of them. Your seafood tower? Whole Red Lobster, please. That should be a standard. Now, keep talking. It's a $14.00 seafood tower. And this has to be from the far end of the seafood tower good-ness wagon. A $14.00 shrimp. This isn't even fully two bites. Two bites! Not a meal for a grow adult. $14.99 for a second meal for my twins. Mr.
name: Kathleen Spencer

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text:
This place is fairly new and it's nice with free parking and free breakfast complimentary for gold and diamond HI club members.

The rooms on the ground floor where I am is kind of ghetto  it's a small spaced walk way between the parking and me filled with stuff (bikes, chairs, flower pots and watering cans) doesn't smell good as well. I mean let's face it it's more fun for kids to ride their bikes into a pyramid of traffic cones than off the edge off a concrete walk way.
name: Jeffrey Clark

title: The LINE LA
text:
I was in town early and expected the price to be high. I was surprised at first to fill out an information card.

Staff walking through the room and a cleaning staff that really cleans. At first the two were separated and I thought the card meant I had to leave. After speaking with the staff I understand it cuts down on key cards going missing.

Lots of loud children and a cold pool didn't hurt my feelings either.

Rooms are clean and beds are comfortable.
name: Kirsty Jennings

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: Staff was very helpful to us. We lost a wallet at a restaurant and the manager in the store found and returned it. Thanks for the great service.
name: Teresa Harris

title: Bowlero Cherry Creek
text: Rad place, has all the bells and whistles. It's dirty, but then again its a bowling alley, so we come to bowl. (pun intended) ALL of the staff is incredibly nice, awesome music and ambience. Large place with lots fo food choices. Forever customer!
name: Nicole Khan

title: Wyndham Garden Cross Lanes Charleston
text: So cool. Owners are awesome. Cabins are real log cabins, not just a room with a log exterior. Cabins are small but have all the amenities. Had 30 amp and 50 amp options. The tiny restaurant was pretty good too. Great amenities like heated bath tiles and a jacuzzi tub. Friendly lighting inside and out, and plenty of parking. Would definitely stay again!
name: Kyle Green

title: RODEO MEXICAN RESTAURANT
text: They have a few Americans and other Westerners there. They do have English speaking wait staff. Nothing that can't be handled. The non-Mexican fare is not as good. Taste like Fox Del Montero's The quesadillas and chimichangas are good.
name: Kelly Simpson

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text: Really nice place!  Ive never been to a hostel before so I went in expecting a dorm as I was under the impression (wrongfully so) that this is what a hostel is.  I had a room with a bed and a TV for about 15 USD closer to the weekend.  I booked this place for a concert and I stayed here for 4 nights and essentially it was a hotel for the cost of a hostel.
name: Geoffrey Edwards

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: The food and service are great every time.
name: Conor Cox

title: Hungry Howie's Pizza
text: This is my first time ordering here since I was in the area. I ordered the 3 cheeser pleaser from their speciality pizza and wow! I tell you, it was amazing plus very cheesy!! This is now my go to pizza place and will come back again.
name: Edward Vixayvong

title: RODEO MEXICAN RESTAURANT
text: Good food and service. Nice little restaurant.
name: Rick Broyles

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text: Great service,extremely clean n nice atmosphere! Slightly pricey, but overall very satisfied with my experience!
name: Sally Hooper

title: The Edge Paintball Experience
text: Great place to have a blast!
name: Lauren Clarke

title: Denver Zoo
text: Great family time! No matter the ages, the zoo is always a good time!
name: samantha Finn

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: Overall great experience.  Food was very good in the Red River or Prairie Bistro for dinner and for breakfast in the Frontier Dining Room.  Super friendly and cheerful wait staff.  Hotel is beautifully designed with River stones from the Red River Valley.  Comfortable beds with crisp white linens.  Great view from the dining room.  Excellent complimentary workout room.  Free coffee in lobby from 6-8am.  Amazing dog friendly venue:  48 hour cancellation policy applies to pet friendly rooms. Pets up to 100 lbs are allowed. VALID ALL YEAR
name: Carly Marsh

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text: Super nice staff, the sushi and the experience was amazing! Lol and getting a prize was really fun!
name: Ginger Proud

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: Fantastic food, good service
name: Nicola Wright

title: Crowne Plaza Shenandoah - Woodlands Area, an IHG Hotel
text: This is a really good place, and they have a really awesome service. Everything is good and clean. This hotel is warm and smells really good.
name: Roxana Betancourt

title: Vallarta's Mexican Restaurant
text: Great family place! They have really good memories!!!
name: Thomas Ward

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text: I'm being generous with my rating as the room we stayed in didn't have a security latch for the door and there was a hole in the shower. The sheets were so bad that we're glad to have brought our own blankets and we slept on top of the beds. The breakfast was sub par but at least it was provided.
name: Kadillak Williams

title: Historic Route 66 Motel
text: Great price, great rooms, great location!
name: Dale Jones

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Since there was only 16 rooms, they served breakfast buffet at the restaurant next door. It was very delicious
name: Nathan Hughes

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Came in for a bite. The food was amazing! Prices, portions and taste are spot on. This is our new go to spot! Sanity is restored!
name: Hazel Bryan

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: This hotel is SO NICE. They deadass have an espresso machine with almond milk & syrups. Their breakfast is luxury level delicious. The rooms are clean and have good views. The staff here is very friendly and keep to themselves but are very helpful when needed. The bar is great and all of the bartenders that served me were super kind and great conversationalists. Coming from someone who was in the service industry for 2.5 years their kitchen and their bar space is very clean and organized. Would definitely stay here again, it feels like home.
name: Payten Vincent

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Won a few grand and went home great fun.
name: Harold Garrett

title: Breakout KC Escape Room | River Market
text: Don't miss this hole in the wall! Next corporate or school outing? That's an unequivocal yes! Each room is crafted with care that continually surprised us. Each time we thought we were close, we were dead wrong and were blown away with the next step. Bring your family, coworkers, friends, and anyone else who doesn't mind being locked in a room with you for an hour. (You aren't really locked in). The suspense was real and we finished with just 18 seconds left. Difficulty was perfect. This is a great way to spend an hour.
name: Ukvayat Hanak

title: Hampton Inn & Suites Orange Beach/Gulf Front
text: Stayed here the night before our cruise.  Fairly new property.  The room was great and the view amazing.
name: George Stevenson

title: Marhaba Grill
text: Love love love the food. What an incredible price for all you can eat food. Lamb shank was just perfect. Fish was fall off the bone. Spices were just incredible. Place is not super pretty and ambiance is nonexistent but go for the incredible dishes.  I am still giving it a 5 star and coming back every time I am in the cities.
name: Jade Fang

title: Denver Zoo
text: It was awesome. The animals had a huge space and was super healthy. We can see all until the animals had a nice yard. The painted duck was on the pond like usual but that one has a mean spirit.
name: Jason Thompson

title: Frankie's of Charlotte
text: So much fun but whew expensive!  The game prices are intentionally misleading so you can't really plan on how much you're spending. Bowling is expensive so are the rides. Bumper cars were 6 for example.  Great for dates maybe but if you have a lot of kids skip this place try spare time down the street.  My 1 child was about 40 for bumper cars and a handful of games. Too much.  I will say that it is very clean and the staff is friendly.
name: Crystal Graham

title: Lalibela Ethiopian Restaurant
text:
First Ethiopian experience was a plus! We did the vegetarian entree sampler for 3. Was nice to try 8/9 vegetarian entree options they had! From what I could tell, the injera was super fresh and good bread/utensil!
Flavors were very diverse! Fresh veggies and they were all pretty al dente. Love that they were firm and not overly soggy like a lot of veggies in stews like that can be. Service was slightly slow but completely acceptable and worth it! Just plan to spend some time here.
name: Trenda Martin

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: Awesome museum with great hands on activities the entire family can enjoy. Wandered around for over an hour easily but didnt really make it passed half the first floor! A must do while in Louisville!
name: Lesley Greenwood
